First Half P — Quinn Matthews (Sean Baruch) 4;36. W — Sean Harvey (UA) 6:56. P — Mike Holmes (UA) 21:04. P — Jamie Rosiello (UA) 25:00 
Second Half Saves: W- Brayden Chevillet 7, Anthony Dondiego 5; P- Jon Bile 3 Volleyball 
TACONIC 3, ST. JOSEPH 0 
In Pittsfield, Taconic's serving led the Braves to a 25-17, 25-13, 25-19 sweep of St. Joseph. 
The Braves fired off several aces and used well-placed serves to keep St. Joe's offense out of sync. 
Mya Wiles led Taconic with five aces and three digs. Alexis Huxtable had three kills and five digs. Lilly Garrity had four kills, one block, one ace and one dig. Leanne Hamilton led St. Joe (2-13, 1-6) with three kills, four digs and six assists. Ilyssa Creamer had three aces, two kills, three digs and four assists. Colleen Baker had two kills, four digs and one ace. 
WAHCONAH 3, LENOX 0 
In Lenox on Wednesday, Wahconah earned a 25-15, 27-25, 25-17 sweep over Lenox. 
Hailey Parker led Wahconah with eight digs, 20 assists and three aces. Chloe Warren had six digs, seven assists and two aces. Audrey Pierce had five kills and seven aces. 
Emma Lynch led Lenox with 18 digs. Morgan Levesque had 20 assists and three digs. Cami Smachetti had four assits, eight kills and three digs. 
"Very good game. We just fell short," Lenox coach Bessena Cabe said. "They have a tough front-middle, which we struggled to cover. We definitely adjusted in the second set to their approach and hits."
